Re: English pet peeves
by Embereyes » Sat 11.06.2010 12:32 pm Here's a question for anyone:When you are telling someone to put a letter in a word, would they say "put an h", or "put a h". Technically, the h's phonetic name starts with a vowel, so you would say an h. But the written representation obviously does not start with a vowel. I personally think an h works best, but what about you?
