by Hyperworm » Sat 11.06.2010 1:18 pm I was just thinking about that the other day when I noticed I'd written "a honorific" in one of the topics here ^^; Then I looked down the topic and saw there were a couple other cases of the same thing...I'd definitely tend to use "an". As for why I wrote "a honorific" that time... maybe because I don't say the word 'honorific' often in real life, I connect with the written form more than the pronunciation? So I wasn't really thinking about the pronunciation when I typed the word ^^;
